                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-1406" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE ADAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my father, James Adams. On the 16th July, at half-put nine at night, I was in front of Mr. Billing's house, next door to Mr. Dawson's shop—I saw the prisoner and a boy with him—the boy stood by Mr. Griffin's shop, which is next door to my master's, and two doors from Mr. Daw ton'a—the prisoner came and stood by Mr. Dawson's about five minutes—some ladies came into the shop, and the prisoner took a piece of bacoft off the sideboard, and ran off with it.</p>
